Data Analyst / Data Scientist
Data Analyst at Infinite Nepal with hands-on experience in delivering analytics solutions on large, real-world datasets. Strong proficiency in SQL and Python, with experience working on US healthcare insurance data and building data-driven insights for business stakeholders. Motivated to grow into a Data Engineering-focused role by building scalable, reliable, and high-performance data systems that support advanced analytics and decision-making.

Skills
- Data analysis and interpretation
- Problem-solving and critical thinking

- Root cause analysis and Translating business requirements into technical solutions
- Programming & Querying: Python (NumPy, Pandas, TensorFlow), SQL (Oracle, MySQL, SQL Server), R
- Data Engineering & Analytics: ETL processes, data preprocessing, feature engineering, data validation
- Visualization & Reporting: Matplotlib, Seaborn, Streamlit dashboards
- Machine Learning: Model optimization, anomaly detection, unsupervised learning
- Domain: US Healthcare Insurance Data Analysis

Projects
Anomaly Detection in NEPSE Stock Market Using Autoencoders
- Developed an unsupervised deep learning framework to detect anomalies in NEPSE stock market data using LSTM, BiLSTM, and CNN Autoencoders.
- Collected and preprocessed 9 years of NEPSE index data; created time-series sequences and built reconstruction-based anomaly detection models.
- Designed and trained multiple autoencoder architectures to identify unusual market behavior (e.g., price surges, crashes, COVID-19 impact).
- BiLSTM Autoencoder achieved the best performance with the lowest reconstruction error and accurate anomaly identification.
- Implemented Python-based pipeline using TensorFlow, Pandas, and Matplotlib; applied statistical thresholding for anomaly classification.
- Demonstrated applicability of autoencoders for real-time market monitoring and early warning systems in emerging markets.
